<h3>Experience Summary</h3>
<p>
<b>At Yahoo:</b>
<ul>
<li>
Apache Hadoop: A fault-tolerant and open-source infrastructure for
performing large-scale distributed computing on commodity hardware. Member
of the team that owns GridMix3, a production-load simulator and stress-tester
for Hadoop clusters.
</li>
</ul>
<p>
<b>At Oracle:</b>
<ul>
<li>
Oracle Enterprise Manager: A product used to manage and monitor systems
deployed in an organisation. Member of the team that maintains the patching
feature. Security Point of Contact (SPoC) for the team.
</li>
<li>
Oracle Software Packager and Universal Installer: The tool-set used to
create installers for Oracle's products like the RDBMS and the
Application Server. Team member.
</li>
</ul>
<p>
<b>At Headstrong:</b>
<ul>
<li>
TradePort: An order-management system
for brokerage firms and trading houses that supports multiple
order destinations and has a comprehensive risk management
system. Principal designer of the Common Service Framework
for TradePort Server services.
</li>
</ul>
<p>
<b>At Torry Harris:</b>
<ul>
<li>
ASPizer:
Provided an infrastructure over a J2EE-based application server that
let Application Service Providers (ASPs) manage their users, security,
licensing, billing, etc. Completely distributed environment with
remote administration capabilities and a handy web-based administration
application. Principal architect and designer.
</li>
<li>
WebOBlocks:
Provided a component-based methodology for rapidly building
web applications to be hosted on J2EE-based application servers. Based
on the Model-View-Controller (MVC) architectural pattern. Principal
designer and implementor.
</li>
<li>
Other: dotFlow - a Java-based distributed workflow engine,
EazyCache - a Java-based object cache, a Work-Load Management (WLM)
tool for Distributed CICS, enabling Java/IIOP for Distributed CICS, etc.
</li>
</ul>
<p>
<b>At IBM:</b>
<ul>
<li>
CTF: Designed and built some extensions (a personal finance
management framework, a TN3270 emulator and a WhiteBoard) for the
IBM Consumer Transaction Framework (CTF) developed by IBM Hursley, UK.
Principal designer and implementor.
</li>
<li>
alphaBeans:
Designed and developed some JavaBeans that ultimately
became a part of IBM alphaBeans. This effort spanned four countries
(China, India, Latvia and Belarus) and was managed by IBM USA.
</li>
<li>
AIX Server Support: Provided &quot;Level-3&quot; (L3) support on
the command-line programmes available to AIX customers.
</li>
</ul>
<h3>Personal Projects</h3>
<p>
Here is a list of some of my personal projects:
<ul>
<li>
GCJ: I have been a contributing hacker to the GNU Compiler for Java
(GCJ) in particular and the GNU Compiler Collection (GCC) in general since
2002.
</li>
<li>
GCJ for MinGW: A Windows-native port of the GNU Compiler for Java
(GCJ) using the GNU tool-set as provided by the Minimalist GNU for Windows
(MinGW) project. Based on the work of Adam Megacz.
</li>
<li>
GDB for MinGW: A Windows-native port of the GNU Debugger (GDB) version 5.2.1
using the GNU tool-set as provided by the MinGW project. Based on the patches
from Artem Khodush.
</li>
<li>
ZINC: A simulator-cum-assembler for playing a variant of Core War.
</li>
<li>
VirtualTaj: A 3D interactive walkthrough of the famous Taj Mahal for
Windows and Linux, developed using OpenGL and SDL.
</li>
<li>
The Hobbitware.com Intranet Project: A guide to setting up a
complete intranet for a small organisation using free server software on
Linux, based on personal experience.
</li>
<li>
x86 Disassembler: An intelligent disassembler for producing valid assembly
language programmes from MS-DOS executables.
</li>
<li>
Fox3D: A simple raycasting 3D engine for walking through a
maze, similar to the legendary game Wolfenstein 3D by id Software.
</li>
<li>
PMars: A simple voxel landscape engine inspired by the legendary
&quot;Mars&quot; demo by T. J. Clarke, written almost entirely in assembler
and using the x86 Protected Mode under MS-DOS.
</li>
<li>
Core War: Another assembler and simulator created earlier for working
with Core War programmes as described by A. K. Dewdney.
</li>
<li>
Others: An assembler/simulator for Knuth's MIX, a fast Mandelbrot set
explorer, etc.
</li>
</ul>
